description: This is an easy trail to hike but it is rated average because of the length. For the most part it follows along the lakeshore with a few minor diversions through the bush. Nice views of the lake and Kananaskis Falls and Sarrail Falls. While you're there take some time and feed the whiskeyjacks.NTS Map: 082J11Elevation Gain: 60 m (197 ft).
directions: Park at the interlakes parking area in Peter Lougheed Provincial Park and follow the trail in either direction. Other trails branch out from this one, just stay near the lakeshore.
title: Upper Kananaskis Lake Loop
